      <TextArea fx:id="definitionTextArea" layoutX="59.0" layoutY="72.0" prefHeight="407.0" prefWidth="595.0" text="Reflexive-If every node has a self loop&#10;Symmetric-If whenever there is an edge(a,b) then (b,a) is also an edge&#10;Anti Symmetric-If whenever (a,b) is an edge and (b,a) is an edge then (a) must be the same as (b)&#10;Transitive-If (a,b) is an edge and (b,c) is an edge then (a,c) must be an edge&#10;Equivalence-The graph is reflexive, symmetric and transitive&#10;Partial Order-The graph is reflexive, antisymmetric and transitive&#10;Simple Graph-The undirected graph contains at most one edge between any 2 nodes and no self loops.&#10;Multigraph-The undirected graph contains multiple edges between node pairs but no self loops.&#10;Pseudograph-The undirected graph contains self loops and multiple edges between node pairs.&#10;Complete Graph-The graph contains an edge between every pair of distinct nodes&#10;Connected-The graph contains a path between every pair of distinct nodes&#10;Acyclic-The graph contains 0 cycles(cycles must contain at least 3 nodes)&#10;Bipartite-The graph can be divided into 2 disjoint node sets so every edge connects a node from one set to the other&#10;Tree-The graph is connected and acyclic&#10;Euler Circuit-The graph contains a circuit that traverses every edge of a graph exactly once and returns to start&#10;Directed Simple Graph-The directed graph contains at most 1 edge between any 2 nodes and no self loops&#10;Directed Multigraph-The directed graph contains multiple edges between node pairs and no self loops&#10;Directed PseudoGraph-The directed graph contains self loops and multiple edges between any 2 nodes&#10;Complete Digraph-The directed graph contains a directed edge between every vertex to every other vertex&#10;" visible="false" />
